visuals.description:
This is a Processing sketch to simulate the way fireflies synchronize with one another. Each of of the circles represents a single firefly and when another firefly on the screen flashes white, or "fires", the firefly will try and catch up to the firefly that just fired. The world makes many assumptions, so here is a list of some of them:
1) Every firefly can see every other firefly and has 20/20 vision
2) Every firefly starts with the same period
3) Every firefly is influenced additively or linearly by the number of flies firing

visuals.title: Tiny Fibonacci Sphere v2.0
visuals.description:
A fast method of producing an arbitrary number of equally distributed points around a sphere. This is accomplished by drawing a fibonacci spiral (similar to sunflower seed pattern) that maintains constant surface area.

n = number of points
phi = (sqrt(5)+1)/2 - 1
ga = PHI * PI

for each point i (1..n)
longitude = ga*i
latitude = asin(-1 + 2*i/n)

As written, the sketch constantly adds new points to the sphere. Click to toggle this feature, so you can examine the point distribution.

visuals.description:
今回、私は「辺境の世界」をテーマに作品を制作しました。漆黒な世界から、非現実的で奇妙な世界に移動しようとする作品になっております。
　作品作りで大変だったことは、一つの球体を中心に回すことです。始めは、太陽系を作りたかったのですが、惑星を三つしか作れませんでした。そのため、球体を回しながら周りに背景を作ろうと思いました。この結果、奇想天外な作品が生まれました。
　この作品の一番の特徴は、球体を中心に背景が移り変わるところです。現実と非現実の狭間をテイラースウィフトの最新曲を「ME！」を聞きながらお楽しみください。

A world map showing the countries with HDI within an interval. You can choose the interval, navigate throw the years and click on play to see the evolution. It's also possible to see the HDI value of a country when the mouse is over it.

visuals.title: Random palette generator
visuals.description:
A tweak of my last sketch in which I used random colors, but selected random limits in order to get something not too random, with colors that go well together.

It resulted in some interesting palettes so I decided to do something that allows me to see which values produce these colors and experiment with different values.

visuals.title: Langton's ant
visuals.description:
Just a simple implementation of the Langton's ant.

I just wanted to quickly implement it after watching a numberphile video talking about it (http://www.numberphile.com/videos/langtons_ant.html).

But, when I started trying, I kept thinking:  there are too many nested conditionals, there must be a simpler way to do it.

So it became kind of a personal challenge to see how short and simple I could make the code, and the final code doesn't use any conditional clause.

visuals.title: DUO HSB color selector 2
visuals.description:
A new version of my DUO HSB color selector.

I wanted to add the RGB values of the colors (so that they can be selected on software that doesn't have a HSB color picker) and the perceived lightness of the colors (the two half circles on the middle).

I changed the interface too.

Now the hue rings turn, to make it easier to see other color combinations with the same angle.
You can turn each ring or both at the same time by turning the stripped ring.

I also changed the way saturation and brightness are selected to make it easier to see how they affect the colors.
